‚öôÔ∏è Clarification on Upstream Power Assets (Utility Feed, Transformer, Switchboard & Load Devices)

Hi Team,

From our side, as part of the data migration from IFP, CPNG, and FUSE, we were able to retrieve most of the DC and AC assets that are required for forming the power chain in DC Track.
However, during the extraction we noticed that certain upstream assets ‚Äî specifically the Utility Feed, Transformers, ATS/Main Electrical Switchboards, and their connecting Load Devices ‚Äî were not available in the source systems (CPNG/FUSE/IFP).

Because these upstream components were missing, we did not import those assets or their related Excel sheets (Utility Feed, Transformer, Switchboard, and Load Device templates) into DC Track.
To ensure the power-chain continuity and calculation flow still function properly, we started the import from:

DC Plant level for DC Flow

UPS level for AC Flow


These starting points allow the power flow to be accurately mapped even without the upstream utility and switchboard data.

At the same time, we did not import any Equipment assets, since equipment-level data was not available from the source systems.

If you would like to include those upstream elements (Utility Feed, Transformer, Switchboard, and Load Devices) for completeness, we can share sample template sheets that can be used for your reference. You can fill in those details, and we can include them in the next import cycle.

Please review and confirm if you‚Äôd like to proceed with those additional upstream components.

Thanks,
Naveen

